        "last_activity_date": 1320849735,
        "creation_date": 1320849735,
        "body": "<p>If the <code>.jar<\/code> file is a runnable jar from the command line i.e. if you are able to execute <code>java -jar minecraft_server.jar something somethin<\/code>, then you can simply create the GUI and issue <code>java<\/code> commands to the jar using `NSTask'. A good post on StakOverflow is <a href=\"https://stackoverflow.com/questions/412562/execute-a-terminal-command-from-a-cocoa-app\">Execute a terminal command from a Cocoa app<\/a><\/p>\n\n<p>You may also need to monitor the process once running as well.<\/p>\n",
